<HEADLINE>
Government OKs 1st US offshore wind farm
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
BOSTON 2010-04-28 16:07:23 UTC
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
U.S. Interior Secretary Ken Salazar has approved what would be the United States' first offshore wind farm, off Cape Cod.
</P>
<P>
Salazar announced the decision at a news conference Wednesday in Boston.
</P>
<P>
Salazar's decision on the controversial Cape Wind project clears the way for a 130-turbine wind farm in Nantucket Sound off the coast of the northeastern state of Massachusetts.
</P>
